definition: cat/CL:隻|只[zhi1]/(dialect) to hide oneself/(coll.) modem

sentences.english: The wildcat intruded into Chenggong's territory and was caught and killed by her.
sentences.chinese: 據悉，該野貓私闖了“成功”的領地，被抓捕並咬死。

sentences.english: Police said it was a wild cat that strayed into people's homes.
sentences.chinese: 警方表示，其實這是一隻野貓誤闖入民宅。

sentences.english: The Alleycats invite school groups to the farm to help out.
sentences.chinese: 野貓農莊邀請學校團體到農場幫忙。

sentences.english: In western Queensland, army marksmen have been called in to shoot feral cats.
sentences.chinese: 在昆士蘭州西部，已經召集軍隊神槍手射殺野貓。

sentences.english: When Americans say wildcat, they usually mean a lynx, an ocelot or a bobcat.
sentences.chinese: 美國人說到野貓，他們通常指的是猞猁。

sentences.english: The frill is that ruff-like collar it uses to bluff its enemies, like feral cats.
sentences.chinese: 皺褶是用於嚇唬敵人的輪狀衣領，就像野貓一樣。

sentences.english: One bank in the state of Michigan offered paper money with a picture of a wildcat on it.
sentences.chinese: 密歇根州一家銀行印製的錢幣上有野貓的圖像。

sentences.english: An alley kitten hangs around the demolished site of an old house in Shanghai, China.
sentences.chinese: 上海，一隻野貓在被拆除的老房子周圍遊蕩。

sentences.english: The moggy is most closely related to the African and European wild cat.
sentences.chinese: 與家貓親緣關係最近的是非洲野貓和歐洲野貓。

sentences.english: The moggy is most closely related to the African and European wild cat.
sentences.chinese: 與家貓親緣關係最近的是非洲野貓和歐洲野貓。

sentences.english: Now then , what say you and I take a visit to this "Wild Cathouse"?
sentences.chinese: 這樣吧，我們一塊去“野貓別墅”怎麼樣？

sentences.english: One day I found a litter of wild kittens in our woodpile.
sentences.chinese: 有一天，我在木柴堆上發現一窩野貓仔。

sentences.english: Walking in the street, it seems to pedestrians, and street talk Wildcats.
sentences.chinese: 在街上散步，看來往的行人，和路邊的野貓說話。

sentences.english: Some wild cats disturbed his vegetable life.
sentences.chinese: 一些野貓打擾了他平平靜靜的生活。

sentences.english: The dog struggled fiercely with the wild cat.
When the wildcat set foot in that place again, he was immediately trussed up by the ropes.
sentences.chinese: 當野貓再一次走到那個地方，它立刻就被粗繩綁起來。

definition: cat/CL:隻|只[zhi1]/(dialect) to hide oneself/(coll.) modem
to cry out/to bark out a sound
to breed (livestock, fish, crops etc)/to grow/to raise
to wander/to roam about/to loaf about/to be idle
dog food/(Internet slang) public display of affection (term used by singles 單身狗|单身狗[dan1 shen1 gou3] forced to "eat" it)
